
[1]subsistency

   SUBSIST'ENCY, n. Real being; as a chain of differing subsistencies.

   Not only the things had subsistence, but the very images were of some
   creatures existing.

   1. Competent provisions; means of supporting life.

   His viceroy could only propose to himself a comfortable subsistence out
   of the plunder of his province.

   2. That which supplies the means of living; as money, pay or wages.

   3. Inherence in something else, as the subsistence of qualities in
   bodies.
